result.execSummary:
The defendant Andrew T Gonring was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Per order of the Court on 2-10-15, Restitution amended to $2,286.50 plus the 10% surcharge, a sole obligation.  
Any bond on file in 14-CF-383 shall be applied to outstanding financial obligations in 14-CF-76.

$243 court costs imposed in 14-CF-383 shall be paid as a condition of probation in 14-CF-76.
If probation is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall have no contact with MAJ or her family.
Defendant shall have no contact with NAG, unless permission from Defendant's Probation Agent.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent.
Defendant shall participate in sex offender treatment and follow any treatment recommendations.
Defendant shall comply with sex offender registration.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent with: any sentence previously imposed.

superMiscConds.notes:
Defendant shall have no contact with MAJ or her family.
Defendant shall have no contact with NAG unless Probation Agent authorizes.

Defendant shall undergo sex offender treatment and follow any recommended treatment or counseling.  
All outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from prison wages at a rate to be determined by the Dept. of Corrections and any balance shall be due as a condition of Extended Supervision or judgment shall be entered.
